About - Lanigan & Associates P.C.                About “Our clients are the center of everything we do. When they succeed, we succeed. Our approach stands the test of time.”Founded in Thomasville, Georgia in 1974, Lanigan & Associates, P.C. (Lanigan) began as a small boutique tax practice with the mission of helping clients solve problems.Bernard Lanigan, Sr. spent many years as the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) for a large publicly traded company, and Bernard Lanigan, Jr. began his career as a member of a “Big 8” firm. From that, our practice was founded on the principles built through extensive public company experience and national accounting firm acumen.  Together, they created a vision to solve client problems through cost effective planning and strategies. In the 40 years since inception, Lanigan has grown into a full-service regional accounting and consulting practice with locations in Thomasville, Tallahassee, and Atlanta. Our firm has grown our practice from two members to over 50 professionals and support staff. One of our greatest strengths is that we possess the size and expertise necessary to take on large and challenging projects in a wide variety of industries, while maintaining a small-firm feel such that we give each of our clients the personal touch and attention they deserve from their trusted advisor. Our PrincipalsView BioBernard Lanigan, Jr., CPAChairmanView BioFrank J. Mercer, CPA, CFPManaging PrincipalView BioC. Bradford Jackson, CPA, CFAPrincipalView BioD. Mark Fletcher, CPA, CFE, CGMAPrincipalView BioG. Thomas Harrison, Jr., CPA, CFPPrincipalView BioJohn W. Keillor, CPA, CIAPrincipalView BioMichael O. Sills, Jr., CPA, CFE, CGMAPrincipalOur ManagersView InfoGlenn Townsend, CPA, CGMASenior ManagerView InfoTom Hoyt, CPASenior ManagerView InfoDona ReetzSenior ManagerView InfoJames S. Shaw III, CPA, CGMASenior ManagerView InfoBryan MillerIT DirectorView InfoKeith Eierhart, CPATax ManagerView InfoAllison BassAccounting Services ManagerView InfoEr